# BoskePulseCore

Swift Package at `BoskePulseCore/`. Shared by app and widget targets.

## Key modules

| File | Responsibility |
|------|----------------|
| `PulseEngine.swift` | Central actor — refresh channels, snapshot assembly, alerts |
| `ServerDiscovery.swift` | Merge Coolify + Hetzner hosts with `serverOverlays` |
| `CoolifyClient.swift` / `HetznerClient.swift` | Live clients + mappers; protocol for tests |
| `HealthProber.swift` / `PrivateNetworkProber.swift` | Public HTTP and Tailscale TCP probes |
| `HealthRollup.swift` | Per-server and overall health aggregation |
| `ConfigLoader.swift` / `Models.swift` | JSON config and domain types |
| `SnapshotStore.swift` | App Group JSON read/write |
| `AlertDebouncer.swift` / `TelegramNotifier.swift` | Alert pipeline |

## Testing

- Add or update tests in `BoskePulseCore/Tests/BoskePulseCoreTests/`.
- Use fixtures under `Tests/BoskePulseCoreTests/Fixtures/`.
- Run: `make test` or `cd BoskePulseCore && swift test`.
- Mock network via protocol conformances — no live API calls in tests.

## Constraints

- No SwiftUI or AppKit imports in core.
- No Keychain access in core — use `CredentialsStore` protocol.
- Polling intervals live in config and `PulseRefreshTiming.swift`.
